    title: 'Masala Dosa',
    image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1630383249896-424e482df921?w=600&h=400&fit=crop',
    category: 'main',
    prepTime: 30,
    cookTime: 20,
    servings: 4,
    difficulty: 'Medium',
    ingredients: [
      { name: 'Rice', amount: '300g, soaked', category: 'Pantry' },
      { name: 'Urad dal', amount: '100g, soaked', category: 'Pantry' },
      { name: 'Potatoes', amount: '4 large', category: 'Produce' },
      { name: 'Mustard seeds', amount: '1 tsp', category: 'Spices' },
      { name: 'Curry leaves', amount: '10', category: 'Spices' },
      { name: 'Turmeric', amount: '1/2 tsp', category: 'Spices' },
      { name: 'Onion', amount: '2', category: 'Produce' },
    ],
    steps: [
      { instruction: 'Grind soaked rice and dal into a smooth batter. Ferment overnight.', instructionFirstSteps: 'Grind the soaked rice and dal separately in a blender to a smooth batter. Combine, add salt, and leave at room temperature overnight to ferment. The batter will double in size and develop tiny bubbles and a pleasant sour smell.', instructionChefsTable: 'Grind dal first to a fluffy, aerated paste, then rice to a slightly grainy batter. Combine with salt and ferment at 28-32°C for 8-12 hours until doubled in volume with visible bubbles and mild acidity.' },
      { instruction: 'Boil and roughly mash potatoes.' },
      { instruction: 'Temper mustard seeds, curry leaves, and onions in oil. Mix with potatoes and turmeric.', instructionFirstSteps: 'Heat oil and add mustard seeds — when they pop, add curry leaves (they\'ll sizzle!) and sliced onions. Cook until soft, then fold in the mashed potatoes and turmeric. The filling should be well-seasoned and slightly chunky.', instructionChefsTable: 'Execute the tadka: mustard seeds in hot oil until they splutter, followed by curry leaves and onions. Cook until translucent. Fold in roughly mashed potatoes with turmeric — maintain textural variation.' },
      { instruction: 'Spread a thin layer of batter on a hot griddle, drizzle oil, cook until crispy.', instructionFirstSteps: 'Heat a flat griddle until very hot. Pour a ladleful of batter in the center and spread outward in circles using the back of the ladle. Drizzle oil around the edges. Cook until golden and crispy with lacy edges — don\'t flip! Dosa is cooked on one side only.', instructionChefsTable: 'Heat the tawa to 200°C. Pour batter centrally and spread in concentric circles to paper-thin. Drizzle oil along the perimeter. Cook until golden-brown with a lace-like pattern and the dosa releases from the surface (2-3 minutes). Do not flip.', duration: 3 },
      { instruction: 'Place potato filling on one side, fold. Serve with sambar and coconut chutney.' },
    ],
    culturalNote: 'Masala Dosa is South India\'s greatest culinary gift. The art lies in the paper-thin, perfectly crispy crepe. Fermentation gives it its distinctive tang.',
